  <description type="morphology">Cypselae columnar to obconic, 3–4.5 mm (tapered to basal callosities, filled by embryos) ribs slightly flared apically; pappi of orbiculate to lanceolate, involute, arcuate (glabrous) scales 2.5–7 mm, 0.5–2 mm longer than cypselae.  2n = 18.</description>
